\fs34 How to get started:\

\fs24 \
You must transfer some files from the distribution folder and put them within folders in\
the SC Server program folder.\
\
The classes folder (or a symbolic link to it) must be placed within the SCClassLibrary folder. \
\
The help files folder should be placed within the Help folder. \
\
You must recompile the library by pressing apple+k (option also under Lang menu). \
\
Finally, in order to run some of the examples, take two breakbeat samples, the first\
8 beats and the second 4 beats long and put them in the Sounds folder in SuperCollider. \
The two samples should have filenames "break" and "break2". You'll see them referenced in \
examples as "break", "break2". If you don't follow this step, the examples won't \
run unless you substitute a valid location of a soundfile on disk.  A few examples also use\
the default "a11wlk01.wav" sample that comes with SC3. \
\
\

